<section id="body">
	<p align="left"><font color="#000000"><b>1</b>  Every year road transport consumed the greatest (…) of petroleum.</font></p><g id="21">A  quantity</g><g id="22">B  amount</g><g id="23">C  proportion</g><g id="24">D  number</g><p align="left"><font color="#000000"><b>2</b>  Petroleum consumption for railways was (…) less than for other means of transport.</font></p><g id="25">A  a lot</g><g id="26">B  far</g><g id="27">C  many</g><g id="28">D  much</g><p align="left"><font color="#000000"><b>3</b>  In 1999 road transport consumed (…) petroleum than the previous year.</font></p><g id="29">A  less</g><g id="30">B  fewer</g><g id="31">C  fewer tonnes of</g><g id="32">D  a smaller quantity of</g><p align="left"><font color="#000000"><b>4</b>  Petroleum consumption by air transport was (…) in 1999 than ten years earlier.</font></p><g id="33">A  many more</g><g id="34">B  much higher</g><g id="35">C  a lot higher</g><g id="36">D  far higher</g><p align="left"><font color="#000000"><b>5</b>  Over the years railway and water transport consumed (…) petroleum.</font></p><g id="37">A  less and less</g><g id="38">B  smaller and smaller amounts of</g><g id="39">C  fewer and fewer</g><g id="40">D  fewer and fewer tonnes of</g><p align="left"><font size="2"></font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb24">
	<p align="left">1D. Petroleum is uncountable.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb27">
	<p align="left">2C. 'Many' is used for countable nouns, while 'less' is used for uncountable nouns. You cannot use the two together.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb30">
	<p align="left">3B. 'Few' and 'fewer' cannot be used with uncountable nouns such as 'petroleum'.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb33">
	<p align="left">4A. The missing word refers to the noun 'consumption', which is uncountable.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb39">
	<p align="left">5C. Petroleum is uncountable. 'Fewer' can be used only with countable nouns.</p>
</section>
